item.title: Ok The Deobfuscator !?!
item.dc:creator: @Morgoth Morgoth
item.description:
@Morgoth wrote:

My current favorite project idea is a SCAR/Java hybrid bot, just because no one has ever made a good (or, for that matter, complete) one.

To that I agree. The best (less detectable) idea is to make a read only java part, that streams vital data (eg. player coords, angle, ground data, interfaces with their onscreen coords etc.) to SCAR, which does the clicking part.
Unfortunately, I must admit, that I don’t have deep enough Java knowledge to do that. Even DEOBed code with all those Class56 and anInt77 are to tricky for me.
